Dear all,

A tenure track position will become available at the Institute for Logic,
Language and Computation, which is part of the University of Amsterdam. We
are looking for female candidates in the direction of Logic and
Computation. Application deadline is Monday 19 March. More information
below.

Best wishes,

Benno

==============================

MacGillavry Fellowship, Tenure Track position for women in Logic and
Computation
Deadline: Monday 19 March 2018
ILLC participates in the recruitment programme at the Faculty of Science
for top level female talent. This programme is named after the ground
breaking crystallographer Carolina MacGillavry, an alumna of the University
of Amsterdam. The MacGillavry Fellowships
<http://www.uva.nl/en/faculties/faculteit-der-natuurwetensch
appen-wiskunde-en-informatica/organisation/macgillavry-
fellowship/macgillavry-fellowship.html>
at the Faculty of Science are offered to women who excel in their
discipline, who possess leadership potential and aspire to a career as a
professor at the University of Amsterdam.
For more information, see here
<https://www.illc.uva.nl/NewsandEvents/News/Positions/newsit
em/9569/MacGillavry-Fellowship,-Tenure-Track-position-for-
women-in-Logic-and-Computation>
or at
www.uva.nl/en/content/vacancies/2017/12/17-656-macgillavry-
fellowship-tenure-track-position-for-women-in-logic-and-computation.html
or contact Prof. Sonja Smets at S.J.L.Smets at uva.nl <S.J.L.Smets@uva.nl>.


